Okay, so I'm currently at (40, 11). I see that there's supposed to be a boulder at (41, 11), but it's displaying as the fountain symbol, `{`. Hmm, that's odd. Let's look at the map: I'm in Row 11, which looks like this: `#.....@{`#.  But the fountain is at (41,11). Actually, I think I'm *on* a fountain, because the map showed I was at the fountain when I was at x=41.  However, let's keep track of those coordinates.

The map shows a boulder at (42, 11) - that's marked by '`'. Alright, I need to push boulders onto fountains. Fountains are indicated by `{`.  There's one at (42, 10) in Row 10, and another at (41, 11) in Row 11.

There's a boulder right now at (42, 11). Can I push that? Well, (43, 11) is a `#`, so I can't push it East.  (42, 12) is also a `#`, so I can't push it North. In fact, if I check row 11 again, it confirms that I am at x=41, a fountain, and the boulder is at x=42.

I am at x=40, y=11.
If I go North to x=40, y=10. Then East to x=41, y=10. Then East to x=42, y=10 (which is a fountain). Then South to x=42, y=11 (boulder). We can push it South? Row 12, x=42 is `#`. I can't push it South.
I can push it West! But, x=43 has a `#`. I can't move there.

